{"title": "Morality of Marriage and Other Essays on the Status and Destiny of Woman", "description": "In this series of essays, British feminist and novelist Mona Caird discusses marriage customs at various points in history, offers thoughtful and informed criticisms of the state of marriage in the Victorian era, and debunks prevailing sexist beliefs of her time. She advocates for an equal partnership between wives and husbands and calls for the reform of the relations between the sexes, sharing her vision of a future society that affords women greater dignity and freedom. (Summary by Scarbo)", "duration": 30573, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "10984", "name": "Mona Caird"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/moralityofmarriage_2302_librivox/morality_2302.jpg", "copyright_year": "1897", "genres": ["Essays & Short Works"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Scarbo"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "J. M. Smallheer"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Scarbo"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Introduction", "readers": [17916], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/moralityofmarriage_2302_librivox/moralityofmarriage_00_caird_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1917}, {"section": 1, "title": "1. The Emancipation of the Family. Part 1: Early History of the Family", "readers": [17471], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/moralityofmarriage_2302_librivox/moralityofmarriage_01_caird_64kb.mp3", "duration": 2722}, {"section": 2, "title": "1. The Emancipation of the Family. Part 2: The Patria Potestas", "readers": [16529], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/moralityofmarriage_2302_librivox/moralityofmarriage_02_caird_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1561}, {"section": 3, "title": "1. The Emancipation of the Family. Part 3: The End of the Patriarchal System", "readers": [16209], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/moralityofmarriage_2302_librivox/moralityofmarriage_03_caird_6